description:
File: rust/lichen-senml/src/cbor.rs
Lines: 379-426 (skip_one_depth function)

The skip_one_depth function handles major types 0-5 and 7, but returns InvalidInput for major type 6 (CBOR tags). RFC 8949 defines tags as a valid CBOR construct, and some SenML encoders may wrap values in tags (e.g., for epoch-based time per RFC 8943, or for typed arrays).

When an unknown map key has a tagged value, skip_one fails with InvalidInput instead of skipping the tagged item correctly.

Impact: Decoder rejects valid CBOR containing tags, causing interop failures with encoders that use CBOR tags.

Fix: Add case for major type 6 in skip_one_depth:
```rust
6 => {
    // Tag: consume the tag number, then skip the tagged content
    let mut cur = pos + adv;
    cur += skip_one_depth(data, cur, depth + 1)?;
    Ok(cur - pos)
}
```
